subSubSection.paragraph:
The preserved animals studied have a firm, smooth body. The body profile is high and the dorsum has ridges arranged in a reticulate pattern (
Fig. 8
). There are pronounced tubercles at the ridge junctions. The gill and rhinophoral pockets are smooth. The ground color of the dorsum and foot is white. There are spots of dark pigment on the dorsum and along the mantle edge. Along the mantle edge of the preserved animal there are also perpendicular dark lines that extend nearly to the mid dorsum. The rhinophores are tapered towards the tips. No pigmentation is present on the preserved animals.

