subSubSection.paragraph:
The buccal mass is not pigmented. The radular sac is elongate and protrudes from the buccal mass. The labial cuticle is smooth and devoid of any jaw rodlets. The radular formula of the animal examined (MNHN SMIB 8 DW182-184) is 27 × 43.0.43. The four outer teeth (
Fig. 9A
) are much smaller than the inner and middle lateral teeth and have no denticles. The middle lateral teeth (
Fig. 9C, D
) are hamate with long, pointed hooks. They have a flattened base that overlaps the adjacent tooth. The seven or eight inner lateral teeth (
Fig. 9B
) are smaller than the middle lateral teeth and are arranged in V-shaped rows.
